
[1]greatly

   GREATLY, adv. In a great degree; much.

   I will greatly multiply thy sorrow. Gen.3.

   1. Nobly; illustriously.

   By a high fate, thou greatly didst expire.

   2. Magnanimously; generously; bravely.

   He greatly scorned to turn his back on his foe. He greatly spurned the
   offered boon.
